    "content": "nullSalesforce for Slack Integrations\nTABLE OF CONTENTS\nClose\nClose\nSearch\nSearch\n Salesforce for Slack Integrations\n Which Salesforce Slack App Is Right for Me?\n Enable Salesforce for Slack Integrations\n Add Apps in Your Personal Slack Sidebar\n Sales Cloud for Slack\n PRM for Slack\n Service Cloud for Slack\n Marketing Cloud Account Engagement for Slack\n CRM Analytics for Slack\n Financial Services Cloud for Slack\n Salesforce for Slack\n Connect Salesforce for Slack to a Salesforce Org\n Permission Scopes for Salesforce for Slack\n Slack User Mappings\n Approvals in Slack\n Multi-Org Management in Slack\n Slack Record Layout\n Unfurled Links in Slack Messages\n Trailhead App for Slack\n\nYou are here:\n\nSALESFORCE HELP\nDOCS\nSALESFORCE FOR SLACK INTEGRATIONS\nSalesforce for Slack\n\nSalesforce for Slack authenticates across Salesforce for Slack apps all at once, per org, to simplify access to core Salesforce services.\n\nREQUIRED EDITIONS\nAvailable in: Lightning Experience\nAvailable in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions\nConnect Salesforce for Slack to a Salesforce Org\nUse Salesforce for Slack to authenticate across Salesforce for Slack integrations. After you connect the app to Salesforce, you don’t need to authenticate to the other apps in your workspace.\nPermission Scopes for Salesforce for Slack\nThe Salesforce for Slack app uses a set of permission scopes to read, write, and interact with Salesforce.\nSlack User Mappings\nThe Salesforce for Slack shared user mapping enables a Slack user to authenticate to a Salesforce org one time for all Salesforce for Slack integrations. The apps must be installed in the same Salesforce org within the same Slack workspace. When a user authenticates successfully to Salesforce for Slack, the user mapping is created.\nApprovals in Slack\nWith Salesforce for Slack, you can manage your approvals from within your Slack workspace. Typically, a user creates a record in Salesforce and submits it for approval. The assigned approvers receive a request notification in Slack, enabling them to approve or reject the request.\nMulti-Org Management in Slack\nConnect up to five Salesforce orgs to a single Slack Workspace with the Salesforce for Slack Multi-Org management feature.\nSlack Record Layout\nTailor your customer experience with field-level personalization and quick actions by using Slack Record Layouts.\nUnfurled Links in Slack Messages\nUse URL unfurling to preview record home page details for standard objects in Slack when sharing salesforce.com or force.com links. Unfurling doesn’t account for non-record home links such as object home list views. URL unfurling is supported by the User Interface API.\nDID THIS ARTICLE SOLVE YOUR ISSUE?\nLet us know so we can improve!\nYes\nNo\n ",
